  • Kevin Kane
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Fits like a glove, easy to install
    Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2025
    Color: White
    The Nest thermostat fits into the wall plate cover nicely, and it was easy to install (less than five minutes). If you already have the Nest thermostat installed, it's helpful to take a picture of how the wires connect into the ring behind the thermostat before you... See more
    The Nest thermostat fits into the wall plate cover nicely, and it was easy to install (less than five minutes). If you already have the Nest thermostat installed, it's helpful to take a picture of how the wires connect into the ring behind the thermostat before you remove them.

    Steps:
    1) Gently pull the thermostat off the wall - it will snap off of the ring.
    2) Take a picture of how the wires connect into the ring so you can reconnect them correctly later.
    3) Push the tab for each wire connector and gently pull the wire out.
    4) Use a screwdriver to remove the ring from the wall.
    5) Fit the ring into the wall plate cover, then place back on the wall and screw it in with the same screws you removed in step 4.
    6) Reinsert the wires into the wire connector using the picture you took earlier as a guide.
    7) Snap the thermostat back into place. Make sure it's firmly seated.

    That's it. You may see a couple of messages on the thermostat like "provide stable power source", or "WiFi not connected", but those went away within 30 seconds and then I could see the thermostat in my Google Home app again.
